  "instructions": [
    "preheat the oven to 400.degree.f.\n",
    "season the duck with chinese five spice powder, brown sugar, allspice, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt.\n",
    "heat 1 tablespoon of coconut oil in a large cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat.\n",
    "sear the duck until browned, about 5 minutes per side.\n",
    "remove the duck from the skillet and set aside.\n",
    "add the remaining 1 tablespoon of coconut oil to the skillet.\n",
    "add the onions and garlic and cook until the onions are translucent, about 5 minutes.\n",
    "add the scotch bonnet peppers, thyme, and chicken broth to the skillet.\n",
    "bring the mixture to a simmer and cook until the liquid has reduced by half, about 5 minutes.\n",
    "flake the duck into the skillet and stir to combine with the onion mixture.\n",
    "add the aleppo pepper and paprika to the skillet.\n",
    "cook for an additional 2-3 minutes, until the duck is heated through.\n",
    "serve the duck hash hot, garnished with chopped fresh herbs if desired.\n"
  ],
